Brandon, Angel Incarnate; 3RW

The exiling angel is a fun idea. It reveals a problem with the color pie, though—it’s also a similar design to Hostage Taker. Exiling things to steal them feels very red, but blue and black have been given license to similar abilities. Black blue and green aren’t restrained enough and can often step on design space the other colors could explore. I think Leovold is a realistic mono white card. Mind’s Dilation should be red, not blue. The new Mistcaller Merfolk encroaches on white’s Containment Priest and Hallowed Moonlight effects. Frankly, I think Underrealm Lich’s draw selection should be the solution to white and card draw problems. Instead of raw advantage, white could have advanced selection. But nah, Golgari gets it instead. Colors need better barriers. They’re getting more flexible in ways I consider damaging
